choices.text:
to walk 2km up the street and catch a cab down at the last minute, or ride 2km up the street and catch one coming down. Trains to and from the FMV reserve are the same deal. The path to get to the railroad station is 250km long (France is kind of big) with three stations in between, and we want to start with the one closest to home. So….it will take 20 trains to get to France and fourteen to get home. I would say that looks pretty good in terms of the likelihood of missing a connection or overbooking on the train. Why spend a fortune to fly to New York in admirals club when you can spend $12/day and use the LIRR, Metro North, and Amtrak?

We like to pack snacks and/or monosodiumglutamate (MSG) sandwiches for the train and also resist the temptation to buy expensive food at the train station.

But Muñoz is not entirely convinced that things are set on the airline, so we will try again later. I’m going to send her an email with the screenshot as well….

2020 Mar 27: So I was looking at a virtual flight on United with no reward seating privileges and found they don’t even list AVOD, US air is back to zero fare conversion and the train maybe isn’t moving at the pace he wants. But he is confident United will get on track, and we will wait for them. Meanwhile,
